
Overview of noun gallant

The noun gallant has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) dandy, dude, fop, gallant, sheik, beau, swell, fashion plate, clotheshorse -- (a man who is much concerned with his dress and appearance)
2. squire, gallant -- (a man who attends or escorts a woman)

Overview of adj gallant

The adj gallant has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) gallant -- (unflinching in battle or action; "a gallant warrior"; "put up a gallant resistance to the attackers")
2. dashing, gallant -- (lively and spirited; "a dashing hero")
3. gallant, lofty, majestic, proud -- (having or displaying great dignity or nobility; "a gallant pageant"; "lofty ships"; "majestic cities"; "proud alpine peaks")
4. chivalrous, gallant, knightly -- (being attentive to women like an ideal knight)
